This paper focuses on studying sockpuppetry in online discussion communities, which involves analyzing posting behavior, linguistic traits, and social network structure. This work falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it deals with analyzing social network structures and interactions between users. Additionally, the paper also involves analyzing linguistic traits, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also deals with deceptive behavior, which can be categorized under the sub-categories of social computing (cs.SOC) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper involves predicting whether a pair of accounts belongs to the same user or not, which falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
